Class GarbledMessageException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • com.camerontec.catalys.core.message.AbstractMessageException

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class GarbledMessageException
extends AbstractMessageException
    Indicates receiving a "garbled" FIX message. Currently only 2 problems indicate a "garbled" FIX message - incorrect FIX message body length or checksum.
    See Also:

    • Constructor Detail

      • GarbledMessageException

        public GarbledMessageException(int code,
                               IFIXMessage fixMessage,
                               byte[] messageBytes,
                               String errorMessage,
                               int msgSeqNum,
                               String msgType,
                               int tagID)
        This constructor allows you to associate a number of extra FIX message values with the exception.

        These extra values are those commonly used in the FIX Session level Reject message.

        Parameters:
        code - Indicates the cause of the "garbling" message exception.
        fixMessage - FIX message which cause the "garbling" message exception.
        messageBytes - message bytes
        errorMessage - Any text associated with the exception.
        msgSeqNum - Message sequence number of related message - null if unknown.
        msgType - Message type of related message - null if unknown.
        tagID - Tag number of relate message field - 0 if unknown.
